{
  "texts": [
    "In 84% of the experiments, we validated at least one SD hit and got a DR readout.",
    "The median activity for the total of 144 DR measurements was 15.4 µM (which compares favorably with HTS 25, 74), of which 13% showed sub-µM potency.",
    "Overall, we achieved an average of 2.8 hits per validation study, resulting in a hit rate of 51%.",
    "The false positive rate of 49% observed in these experiments is favorably compared to HTS' which can be as high as 95% 20, 75.",
    "This difference in false positive rates may stem from the comparative ease and robustness of the low-throughput assay format we employed versus high-throughput assay."
  ]
}